  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators propose to test the hypothesis that implementation of a comprehensive
      handoff program (CHP) - i.e., implementation of a computerized handoff tool along with
      teamwork training for internal medicine residents on inpatient units at Walter Reed and
      Madigan Army Medical Centers - will lead to reductions in resident miscommunications /
      medical errors and improvements in workflow and experience on the wards.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Following collection of baseline data on inpatient wards at both hospitals, teamwork training
      will be provided, accompanied by the introduction of a new computerized handoff tool that
      facilitates accurate transmission of data. The effects of this combined intervention on
      safety and workflow will be assessed on the intervention wards at both hospitals as compared
      with the historical control period.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
